The Department of the Treasury has announced $50 million to help underserved small businesses secure financing, while the Small Business Administration has delivered $50 billion to small businesses and has seen record loans to minority businesses. The Biden-Harris Administration is focusing on supporting small businesses and has released data showing a boom in small business applications during their administration. Entrepreneurs of color are benefiting from increased lending and investments in small businesses, with the share of families owning a business increasing by 9%, particularly among Black and Hispanic households. The administration is celebrating Small Business Saturday on November 25th and has already taken significant steps to support small businesses in recent months.